{
  "stem": "18626.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She says, Kinder, look.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We are seeing, she says, the [YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The [YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That means we are seeing the revenge of them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we are going to be, I'm afraid, killed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that was the outcry by many-- not only our family, by many families.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was the pleasure to see them running, falling in the street, the German army.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And where we are-- where are we going?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "What's going to be with us?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Some of our friends, after crossing from Slabodke to Kaunas, there is a bridge.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because underneath was the Valea.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's a lake flowing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So was a iron bridge, a small bridge to cross over.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A lot of the people-- of the Jewish people jumped over the bridge in the water, maybe to save themselves.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But nobody was saved.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The German guard was so strong, and they all machine gunned them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were all taken to the railroad.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were all start [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] pushed in like cattle, with such a force, with such a murder, anger, to the railroad cattle cars.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Not like human beings.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Everything was-- that's why I use a lot that word-- that word, chased.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We were never-- when it came to these type situations, we were all the time chased.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Not walked.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "One was falling on top of the other.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "In, in, in the trains.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I told my mother, before we went into the trains-- because I spoke with some of my friends when we left the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "To my friend Yonkel Weitz, Bianke Weitz, his brother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Chayet, another Ringer.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And David-- Davidson, a Ringer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Four guys.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
